If forced to choose, Togolese women choose a single man over a widower

45 percent of Togolese women say they prefer an unmarried man over a widower when choosing a partner.

Many women in Togo believe that a widower will come with too many responsibilities. In particular, women fear that widowed men just use children as a get-out-of-jail-free card of family and court obligations, should the marriage end.

If you’re trying to divorce in a country that is still male-controlled, remember to update is legal paperwork so you can get your own permanent records! It’ll make the process easier — and protect you from a quickie divorce. Learn More

26 percent of women say a widowed man would be too emotionally burdened from losing a wife

In the case of a divorced woman vs. a widower, 26 percent of those surveyed in Togolese say that they find it too painful to be around someone who has lost a spouse, even if that spouse has passed away.

Only 1 in 5 single Togolese women says they would prefer a man who has recently divorced
